SIMPLE: unitary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unitary
<hw>U"nit*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to a unit or units; relating to unity; <as>as, the
<ex>unitary</ex> method in arithmetic</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of the nature of a unit; not divided;
united.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unitary theory</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>the
modern theory that the molecules of all complete compounds are units,
whose parts are bound together in definite structure, with mutual and
reciprocal influence on each other, and are not mere aggregations of
more or less complex groups; -- distinguished from the <xex>dualistic
theory</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unite</ent>⟦br⟧
